70(stat)+-7.630(syst)deg. The relative impact of potential\nsystematics (statistical) effects increases (decreases) with cutoff. Our\nanalysis gives v consistent with Mogi at 5.2sigma(stat) or 0.5sigma(stat and\nsyst), and a deformation angle consistent at 4.3sigma(stat) or at 0.3sigma. The\nmodule of the vectorial difference between v from the data and Mogi diminishes\nby a factor 7.65+-1.23(stat) or +-5.78(stat+syst) compared with previous work.\nPotential improvements are discussed.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 25 May 2023 12:07:44 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-05-26"}
